        "<p>I had the same problem. It is because <code>Werkzeug 3.0.0<\/code> was released and Flask doesn't specify the dependency correctly (requirements says <code>Werkzeug&gt;=2.2.0<\/code>). This is why, <code>Werkzeug 3.0.0<\/code> is still installed and <code>Flask 2.2.2<\/code> isn't made for <code>Werkzeug 3.0.0<\/code>.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Solution<\/strong>: Just set a fix version for Werkzeug such as <code>Werkzeug==2.2.2<\/code> in your <code>requirements.txt<\/code> and it should work.<\/p>\n",
